@jack @gdb I‚Äôm a fan of Rust. Clearly scales well, given that Discord uses it.For max performance, however, nothing beats tight C with a customized compiler on specialized hardware. Important for max frame rate on vehicle inference computer.Otherwise, we mostly use C++ & Python.

@Kristennetten While it is tempting to focus on one of those arenas as the ‚Äúhard one‚Äù, in fact they are all difficult & important. Tight C & custom compiler too.An inference computer optimized for energy efficiency, reliability & long life is also critical. Can‚Äôt just jam GPUs in the trunk.

@Kristennetten A general solution to self-driving (essentially, real-world AI) requires writing extremely difficult software in the arenas of training, inference, control, analytical tools, data management, hardware optimization & simulation.One of the hardest technology problems that exists.
